The format function produces a string by formatting a number of other values according to a specification string. It is similar to the 
printf function in C, and other similar functions in other programming languages.


format(spec, values...)

> format("Hello, %s!", "Ander")
Hello, Ander!
> format("There are %d lights", 4)
There are 4 lights


> format("Hello, %s!", var.name)
Hello, Valentina!
> "Hello, ${var.name}!"
Hello, Valentina!
